reviews.text: Ordered takeout of a medium combo pizza and the plain Alfredo pasta side. The pizza was good, classic but they did everything right. The pasta though! Really wasn't expecting anything special but it was so garlicy and much more flavor than I expected. The guy at the cash register was super nice. I would definitely get food here again!

Everytime we stay in slo and we always grab ginos!! My kids always ask when where there. Walking distance from multiple hotels ..there pizza is top tier and there pastrami sub is the bomb!!! We always book a room near by

Tried Gino's pizza for the first time today! We got the large BBQ chicken pizza with ranch on the side and some sodas. They had a lot of options, and I'm excited to try more in the future! The Pizza was good and had plenty of chicken. The BBQ sauce was perfect! Not too sweet. The atmosphere was very clean and had a beautiful view of the mountains! I also appreciated the staff's friendliness.

detailedReviews.author: Joan Pedersen
detailedReviews.text: This is a great place to have an easy, casual, fun group gathering!  We just did lunch with a group of about 22 of us there. We used the ‚Äúfront‚Äù area of the restaurant (closest to the street). Lots of room to mix and mingle. They have both booths and bigger tables. We used the big high-top table for all the food. The parking is super easy. It‚Äôs close to Cal Poly (if that matters for you). You don‚Äôt have to deal with parking downtown. The food is good!  We were even able to get a gluten-free pizza with vegan cheese for one of our guests with dietary restrictions. Bill and Mario took great care of us (thanks, guys!!). They do have outside seating if you prefer to be outside. They also have a few arcade games for the kids. I did a drop-in birthday party here a few years ago.  Definitely consider this place for your next group gathering!

detailedReviews.text: Definitely some good pizza üçï.. crust was good and they didn't go cheap on the toppings. They have some games for the kiddos, and beer for the adults.

detailedReviews.author: Andres Pena
detailedReviews.text:
Came here for lunch while visiting SLO, stayed at the hotel across the street. Was very pleasantly surprised by this place. I got the chicken parmesan lunch special and a small cesar salad. I wish I had taken a picture of the plate before I ate it because even the presentation of the dish was excellent. The chicken had a nice crispy-ness to it and was very delicious. The pasta sauce has a lot of flavor. The garlic bread that came with it was perfect: the bread was toasted but still very soft and complimented the sauce very well. The Cesar salad itself impressed me because the Cesar dressing tasted so fresh, it must have been made in house. The overall aesthetics and ambiance of the restaurant is very pleasing and relaxing with a beautiful view of Monterey St.
I truly didn‚Äôt have high expectations for a local pizza place, but this place has set the bar high for a local pizza spot. Don‚Äôt skip this place. My partner said his pizza had generous toppings and the dough was soft and overall very good. I would definitely come here again.

detailedReviews.author: Reagan Rose805
detailedReviews.text: In my opinion this is the Best Pizza in town!

detailedReviews.author: Stewart Ting Chong
detailedReviews.text: We weren't sure what to expect, but if you're looking for friendly, welcoming staff who serve a great fresh house salad and pizza, this is the place. It's nice that they offer individual size pizza. Salad portions are large. Kudos to the staff who were really good.

detailedReviews.author: Lorinda Esparza
detailedReviews.text: We love Gino‚Äôs. We found them down in Buellton originally and then figured out we had one right here in San Luis Obispo. We really enjoy all of their pizza choices. Their meatballs are supposedly very good too, as I buy them for my son all the time and he loves him. Food always taste fresh and delicious. Staff is always very friendly and helpful. The place is kept nice and clean and inviting. Great place for after a game or to bring the kids. Cool game room in the back.

detailedReviews.author: Dylan Ferguson
detailedReviews.text:
everyone was cool and service was good and stuff, but i ordered a personal anchovy pizza and when i got it looked like some one just dumped a whole can of anchovies onto it.

i understand that most people dont like anchovy pizza, and they probably didnt wanna touch the anchovies or whatever. but this is like an 8" pizza were talking about.

there's only supposed to be like 1 or 2 anchovies per slice of pizza. and that not even just my opinion or anything. cause there's like 1600mg of sodium in a can of anchovies.

im not mad or anything, its just like come on. you should be familiar with how to correctly use any toppings on the menu.

detailedReviews.author: Audrey Arnold
detailedReviews.text: Our club had to order a large amount of pizzas last minute due to Costco giving them away. Gino‚Äôs not only took our order but was super kind about it and had the pizzas out very quickly. They offered two drinks to the people picking them up, and were very considerate. Thank you so much to these people for saving our event!
